The paper discusses the use of robots as assistants in warehouses, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm for human intention recognition involves machine learning techniques such as hidden Markov models and Markov decision processes, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The focus on recognizing human intentions also suggests a potential application in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of robots in a warehouse setting involves control and automation systems, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
